description: In this rich and buttery issue, Rose visits Italy, learns how to share ice cream and finds that a way to a man's job is through his stomach!

Before A Fall

Hope Martinez woke up dead this morning. She found her boyfriend murdered in the hallway outside. And to cap it all she was given a limousine and told she had to drive across America, gathering sinners. She hoped it wouldn't get any worse. She knew it would.
name: Before A Fall

description:
Star Wars Insider 167 profiles the saga's newest heroine: Rey! We go behind-the-scenes on the return of Han Solo in the new Marvel comic book, present an exclusive chat between authors Claudia Gray and Chuck Wendig whose books bridge the original and prequel trilogies, and meet the makers of LEGO Star Wars: The Freemaker Adventures, plus much more!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverPhoto1
REPreviews Exclusive Variant CoverPhoto2

The Dreams of Secret Cinema

"After the projectors have been shut off and the TV screens have dimmed, unwatched films dream..."

The Dreams of Secret Cinema cracks open familar stories and lets free the things hidden inside.

Produced from visual notes of the details and backgrounds of films, I invent a new narrative from those images, to tell a secret story that had been waiting within the film all along. Who would have thought Purple Rain contained a teen ecological espionage movie? Who would have expected that Around the World in 80 Days hid a story about a socialite's bored descent into prostitution?

This edition is an update of Strip For Me 32, raising the number of contained strips from twenty to fifty, including never before seen pages created especially for this release.
name: The Dreams of Secret Cinema

description:
Summer: Chapter 4

Chapter 4 develops the further adventures of 'Teach English in Japan' focusing on the first of two Mount Fuji climbs. The story is based on Jeff and Jonathon's experiences teaching English in a foreign country. Jeff taught in the city of Kofu, Japan for two and a half years. Jonathon taught in Myauli and Taoyuan, Taiwan for a year and a half. They work collaboratively on the scripts, and Jeff creates the finished art.

It is their hope that this comic will give an accurate depiction of the trials and tribulations of living and working in a different culture. This story takes place in the year 2004 and is set to cover one year of life abroad for James K and James F.
name: Summer: Chapter 4

description:
The Dragon Tooth Extraction

In Los Angeles, where wizards get their powers from consuming the remains of extinct magical creatures, Daniel Blackland and his crew of thieves are after a big score: The stash of Hollywood mogul and osteomancer, Walter Capstone. But what they find is a houseful of danger, including links to Daniel's violent childhood.

Includes:

Nine-page story

Three-page vignette

Five pages of character pinups
name: The Dragon Tooth Extraction

description:
A bold new story featuring Roland Deschain and his beleaguered ka-tet on the run following the complete destruction of their beloved city of Gilead! And when such as Gilead falls, the pillars of reality itself - the six beams holding all of existence together - begins to crumble. The satanic plan of the Crimson King to return all of existence to the primal state of chaos is nigh.

Collects Dark Tower: The Battle of Jericho Hill #1-5.
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: Dark Tower: The Gunslinger: Battle of Jericho Hill

description:
In a saloon in the town of Tull, the last gunslinger is approached by a bizarre figure that has a message for him. The essage is terrifying. What's worse, it is delivered by a dead man named Nort whose corpse was animated to serve this very purpose. And that is only the beginning of the horrors awaiting the gunslinger in this strange place deep within Mid-World. We continue Roland Deschain's quest for the Man in Black that has become his obsession.

Collects Dark Tower: The Gunslinger - The Battle of Tull #1-5.
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: Dark Tower: The Gunslinger: The Battle of Tull

description:
The ka-tet of Roland, Alain and Cuthbert have returned safely to their home in Gilead. But all is not well. Roland has kept the evil Maerlyn's Grapefruit and has become obsessed with peering into its pinkish depths despite the deadly toll it's taken on his health. And what the young gunslinger sees brings him the darkest of nightmares. Meanwhile, Roland's father has led a posse in search of those who threatened his son's life in Hambry-John Farson and the Big Coffin Hunters. And in this encounter, Stephen Deschain's life may be forfeit.

Collects Dark Tower: Treachery (2008) #1-6.
name: HC/TPB

description: After witnessing his sister's brutal murder, Jack struggles to cope with the disturbing, psychological aftermath. Scared and alone, he is forced to confront a growing thirst for blood and the harsh reality that either his sanity is quickly crumbling or that he is turning into something else . . . something dark . . . something animal . . .

Wylie Kogan is an aspiring artist, stumping for work in 1963 California. When a fawning fan letter grants him access to his cartoonist hero, the wealthy and celebrated Joseph Ahlstrom, he's quick to take advantage of a proffered portfolio review . . . but winds up learning more than he ever wanted to about Joe when he stumbles across some of his idol's illicit fetish art.

His hasty, ill-considered theft of a drawing triggers a series of events he never planned on . . . most of which involve Joseph's imposing and resolute partner, Roya.

Star Trek's aliens—sometimes allies, sometimes antagonists, always enigmatic—until now! With this new collection of IDW Publishing's first six Alien Spotlight one-shots, featuring creators like comics legend John Byrne, IDWStar Trek editor Andrew Steven Harris and rising stars Scott & David Tipton, readers can for the first time glimpse through the eyes of the aliens for their point of view! Plus, as an added bonus, guest appearances by Captains Janeway, Pike and Terrell! One of the best-reviewed series in IDW's Star Trek line!

Contents

  • Gorn
  • Vulcans
  • Andorians
  • Orions
  • Borg
  • Romulans
name: Volume 1

description:
Cardassians, Kilingons, Q, Romulans, and Tribbles. Five different and distinct alien races, all part of the Star Trek Universe. Alien Spotlight Volume 2 introduces five stand-alone stories that take you on unique and intriguing adventures, each focusing on an alien species that has come into contact — and often conflict — with the Federation of Planets!

Contents

  • Cardassians
  • Klingons
  • Q
  • Romulans
  • Tribbles
name: Volume 2

description: Number 4 in an ongoing scifi noir series.

Comic Shop News is comics' weekly newsletter. Each issue is full-color, 8-12 pages in length, and features CSNsider, news, and interviews. CSN has a complete monthly checklist (complete with PREVIEWS item codes), plus exclusive CSN Hot Picks, 'Fab Firsts,' and a monthly checklist of all the first issues for the month!
Boris’ girlfriend Leena is involved in a Reptilian plot. He really ought to go rescue her. Fine time for Richard to be confined to a hospital bed!
name: Part Four of Five

description: Chaos continues to reign as Detective Amparo Alvarez gains new support for her crusade through the streets of Brooklyn. Brother V's forces grow as he steadily seizes control of the city but hope is on the horizon in the form of a new alliance. With the loss of his dear friend Tiggy and his city under new rule, can our hero bounce back from the brink of death?

The award winning anthology returns with four stories of horror including “Recall Day”, “Miranda’s Quest”, “Date on Time”, and “Realm of the Outcast” with an international cast of contributors. Joining writer E. Mayen Briem are artists Alfer Malaca, Stefan Dagur, Loki Yarison, Ger Cuti, Alonso Ruiz, and Yair P.T.

When the FBI closes Desmodus, Lukos, Francesca, Rags and Gilda's monsters-only school, they are forced by their parents to attend a public school to continue their education. Now, they must try to fool their classmates and faculty all while navigating the horrors of growing up!

Issue 5 includes the stories:

JUlCE!

Written by Nicholas Doan

Art by Daniele Serra & Bobby Timony

PARTY ANlMAL

Written by Caanan Grall & Nicholas Doan

Art by Cal Moray

The Hidden World Part 2

OBSKURA is a science fiction adventure within the frame of Ancient Aliens meets Fringe. It parts from the premise that all mythological tales, the paranormal, and unexplained phenomena we have recorded through the years are not only real, but they all come together to secretly shape humanity. It will share light on the origin of creatures found in our myths and legends while establishing the origins of life on Earth through the eyes of the main character.
name: The Hidden World Part 2

description:
Kneading Dough Part 4

The long awaited conclusion to the "Kneading Dough" story line! (It's about time, right?) Catch up with half of our heroes, who just blew up Chip Brown's bakery, trying to solve his murder! Meanwhile the other half must make a last stand against the giant robotic drizzone threatening to destroy Golden Megalopolis! What ridiculousness can all this mean?
name: Kneading Dough Part 4

description:
Fowl Play - Part 2

Part Two of the Fowl Play storyline. Picking up where the story left off in part one, the members of Aphro Physt are placed in a sticky situation by Le Courier and the Alabaster Association, with disastrous outcomes. Bryce Byrd is then forced to decide whether to give up his superhero responsibilities or save his own mother! Will Le Courier and the Alabaster Association finally be brought to justice? Find out here!
name: Fowl Play - Part 2

description:
Join the Fight Part 3

Isaac and his friends make a decision that will change their lives forever ... and may very well determine the fate of our world! But even as they embrace their roles as Protectors, the evil Dissenters prepare to unleash their forces.
name: Join the Fight Part 3

description:
My Quest

It's sad farewells as the two Ravenwood groups split up, one to chase the Rats, the other to deal with the Earl. But there's a third party plotting action as Raulph and Silvermain join to protect the prince with the help of a more than eager servant. It's now up to Klea to find the Seal, but a new face joins the group in the hopes of raising the odds. Pete was skilled enough to be a Lifdell guard but will he be able to face the challenge of riding into battle with the legendary knight E.F. Ravenwood?
name: My Quest

description: Hot on the trail of Christopher Columbus in Cuba, Allie and Kai make a startling discovery that leads to a high speed car chase through the streets of Havana. An unlikely alliance between the Trail team and their adversary gets them back in the game and sets up what promises to be a thrilling series finale.

'Ware the Forest Folk

Rowen becomes side-tracked on a quest that leads him back into the forest from which he came. He knows all too well the dangers of trolls and peculiar damsels in distress, but is he yet ready to confront his second goblin?

One distraction leads to another, leaving Rowen contemplating his original purpose altogether.
name: 'Ware the Forest Folk

description:
If war is still going on in 1947, it is mainly due to the huge catastrophe of 6th June 1944, in Normandy, which was a major setback for the Allies. In the free world, it has since been called the "Disaster Day".

In the fire of an apocalyptic battle, Murnau, a young and brilliant officer of the Luftwaffe in control of a Messerschmitt 262 fighter jet, witnesses the disaster while facing the enemies' assault forces...
name: Disaster Day

description:
Co-published by Mess Bucket Comics:

The descendants of ancient angel/human hybrids, or Arcane, re-discover long dormant abilities that spring to life when Satan appears on earth. God's army (The Ministry) and Lucifer's army (The Demonic Blight) battle each other one last time for all the marbles... Earth and humanity... winner take all.

Beasts and Priests collects for the first time more than ten years' worth of pointillist portraiture of the world's most legendary scene-makers as rendered by Hate collaborator and Glam Warp creator Jim Blanchard. Much of the black-and-white ink work here has previously seen print in some of the world's better alternative magazines and news weeklies, and the large color portraits made with brightly colored industrial stickers have appeared in the more popular art galleries of North America, such as Seattle's critically important Roq La Rue gallery. Portrait subjects include: Duke Ellington, Redd Foxx, Frances Farmer, Patti Page, Shane MacGowan, Lemmy Kilmister, Ron Jeremy, Marcel Proust, Frank Sinatra, Nell Carter, Dean Martin, Tom Jones, Curtis Mayfield, Terry Southern, Jackie Gleason, Amos Milburn, Willie Nelson, Henry Kissinger, Courtney Love, Clint Eastwood, Steve McQueen, Elvis Presley, Raquel Welch, Brigitte Bardot, Mil Mascaras, Andy Warhol, Lee Marvin, Isaac Hayes, Johnny Cash, Bon Scott, Lee Hazlewood, Raymond Chandler, Ennio Morricone, Bill Hicks, Lenny Bruce and Jim Goad. Blanchard's work is often twisted, mutated and ultimately sickly gorgeous, with a pervasive psychedelic tone. Heavily influenced by such underground greats as Robert Williams and Victor Moscoso, Blanchard fuses meticulous craftsmanship with a pop underground sensibility to produce some of the most vivid and striking cartoon art in the world.
name: SC

description: The original Caliber Presents anthology title was one of Caliber Comic's inaugural releases in the 1990s and featured predominantly new creators, many of which went onto successful careers in the comics' industry. In this first volume of the all-new Caliber Presents, Alex Sheikman presents a science fiction tale inspired by the spaghetti westerns of Sergio Leon. Joe Pruett and Ken Meyer Jr. team up on an introspective tale of a mundane life punctuated by tragedy. Jason Walz illustrates a tale of cosplayers at conventions. Sam Costello and Steven Perkins team up for an unexpected look at victims. Gary Reed and Laval Ng show a glimpse from the pages of Saint Germaine's Magus. Renton Hawkey and Nick Barber present a look at the promise of tomorrow. Mark Bertollini and Jerome Eyquem tell a tale of instant time travel. Gary Scott Beatty takes us to the cool age of Jazz and E. Mayen Briem and Emerson Dimaya take us further back for a horror tale during the war years. Ben Sherrill and Rowel Roque show us a futuristic big game hunting trip and for the artist sketchbook feature, Mark Bloodworth from Clive Barker's Hellraiser, Midnight Mortuary, and Deadworld shows off his art.

Life is a Beach

A DAZE WORK follows the lives of Finch and Barry, who work at a pizza place on the Jersey Shore while trying to find their place in the world. Each month, the two friends and a cast of other characters do their best to keep The Plus alive, while wacky customers and constant money problems try to derail their plans.
name: Life Is A Beach

description: In the the late 21st century, the first official contact is made with extra terrestrial life forms. They arrive not as conquerors, but in need of refuge as they run from a superior foe. As they eventually settle on Earth, not all humans are happy to co-exist with them. Tensions grow and conflict arises. With the humanity deeply divided, a new threat reaches Earth. The very same threat that drove the alien refugees from their home planet, in search of a new one. Can the joint human/alien forces resist the onslaught? Who are these invaders? Can the humans overcome their deep divisions and unite against them? Find out as the story of Exilium unfolds.

Five For Fighting

Who are these brave heroes? Where do they come from? And Oh God, what did they do this time?
name: Five For Fighting

description:
Volume 1

One volume containing every goddamn Sherbet story made between 2009 and 2015, including brand new content and bonus art from several renowned comic book creators.
name: Volume 1

description: With his most personal work ever, comic-book legend STAN LEE, founder/CCO of POW! Entertainment, is proud to join science-fiction legend WILLIAM SHATNER and comics great and Deadpool creator FABIAN NICIEZA with illustrators MARIANO NICIEZA And WILSON RAMOS JR. to introduce STAN LEE'S 'GOD WOKE,' a 60 page digital graphic novel published through the new imprint Shatner Singularity.
name: GN

description:
THE UNICORN AWAKENS

The brutal power of the Unicorn is unleashed upon mutants from hell as they seek to devour the boy that seeks the sword.
name: The Unicorn Awakens

description: Late 1940s, a prominent archaeologist charters a flight to Greenland to inspect a new archaeological find. Little does he know that there are others, too, who are interested in this find, and who are willing to go to any length to keep him away. Or is their interest in the pilot of the chartered plane, who seems to have a history of her own? Find out as the race to a groundbreaking archaeological find from the age of Vikings over a thousand years ago ensues.
In this scifi thriller, we try to understand and unlock the mind of a mysterious mental patient who may hold the details to a past and future catastrophe.

Ethan Daniels is a typical bachelor who suffers from one, infallible truth: dealing with the opposite sex can be complicated. One night, he bumps into a mysterious woman who will change his life...and maybe even the world.
name: Volume 1: Conception

description: In the lush, rural backdrop of Pennystown, Ethan and his neighbors lived a peaceful kind of life. Now, things have changed...drastically. Clones, spawned from a mysterious girl, are preying on the townspeople and paranormal activity is escalating into a full-blown catastrophe. As the questions pile on, only one thing remains certain-nothing will ever be the same.
name: Volume 2: Emergence

description: Ethan's girl troubles just seem to keep multiplying... and multiplying and multiplying. The clones, spawned from his one-night stand with a beautiful woman, continue to prey on the women of Pennystown, taking their bodies to a mysterious giant sperm-shaped vessel. In order to find a way out of this nightmare, everyone must stand as one. But when temptation beckons, can the men be trusted?
name: Volume 3: Survival

description: The people of Pennystown struggle to find their way out of an alien bubble that separates their town from the rest of the world. But first, the men must overcome temptations of the beautiful clones that are quickly spreading throughout the town and exterminating the women. In this final installment of four volumes, we learn the final fate of Pennystown and their enigmatic invaders.
name: Volume 4: Extinction
Aus alt mach jung -- das gibt Stunk!
